Description: Fragment of neck and amygdaloid handle of a probably Knidian pottery transport amphora, gradual curve. Clay fine, micaceous red-brown. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 163, 2? Probably trimmed.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1623)
